[assistant] 抽取并记录信息: {"user_identity": "", "user_preference": "", "research_direction": "Intervention: Evaluate the effectiveness of empirical anti-GP antibiotic treatment", "filter_requirements": "Randomised controlled trials (RCTs) comparing one antibiotic regimen versus the same regimen with the addition of an antiGP antibiotic for the treatment of febrile neutropenic patients with cancer", "rejection_reasons": "", "other_info": "Background: Shift in infections among neutropenic patients with cancer to gram-positive infections. Objectives: Assess effectiveness of empirical anti-GP antibiotic treatment in terms of mortality and treatment failure, rate of resistance development, further infections, and adverse events. Search methods: Database searches included Cochrane Central Register of Controlled Trials (CENTRAL), MEDLINE, Embase, LILACS, conference proceedings, ClinicalTrials.gov, and references of included studies. Selection criteria: RCTs comparing one antibiotic regimen vs same regimen with anti-GP addition for treatment of febrile neutropenic cancer patients. Data collection: Two review authors assessed trial eligibility and extracted data using random-effects model with I2 > 50% heterogeneity. Outcomes: Extracted by intention-to-treat; patient-based analysis where possible. Main results: Empirical anti-GP antibiotics tested at onset or persistent fever, reduced failure with modifications (RR 0.72), same overall failure rate (RR 1.00). Glycopeptides associated with reduced resistant colonisation and superinfection rates."}
